thread.title: Dollar Rises on Optimism in Fed Meeting Minutes

author: Ira Iosebashvili
title: Dollar Rises on Optimism in Fed Meeting Minutes
text:
The dollar rose Thursday after minutes from the Federal Reserve’s latest monetary policy meeting suggested the central bank is optimistic on the U.S. economy.
The WSJ Dollar Index, which measures the U.S. currency against a basket of 16 others, was recently up 0.2% at 83.80.
